3.06591v1", "https://the-decoder.com/?p=33011", "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1133972", "oai:arXiv.org:2602.22273v1", "https://the-decoder.com/?p=33196", "https://the-decoder.com/?p=33164", "oai:arXiv.org:2603.11211v1"], "today_date": "2026-03-16", "today_news": [{"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=33273", "title": "AI consultant uses ChatGPT, AlphaFold, and Grok to find a possible treatment for his dog's cancer", "summary": "An Australian AI consultant used ChatGPT, AlphaFold, and Grok to find a possible treatment for his dog Rosie's incurable cancer. The story went viral after high-profile AI executives like OpenAI's Greg Brockman and Deepmind's Demis Hassabis shared it as proof of what AI can already do.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/ai-consultant-uses-chatgpt-alphafold-and-grok-to-find-a-possible-treatment-for-his-dogs-cancer/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 8}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=33179", "title": "RL agents go from face-planting to parkour when researchers keep adding network layers", "summary": "While most reinforcement learning algorithms use two to five network layers, a research team achieved 2x to 50x performance gains by scaling network depth up to 1,024 layers in a self-supervised agent and saw entirely new behaviors emerge in the process.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/rl-agents-go-from-face-planting-to-parkour-when-researchers-keep-adding-network-layers/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 7}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=33260", "title": "OpenClaw-RL trains AI agents \"simply by talking,\" converting every reply into a training signal", "summary": "AI agents usually throw away valuable feedback from everyday interactions. Princeton's new OpenClaw-RL framework changes that by turning live signals from chats, terminal commands, and GUI actions into continuous training data. The researchers say just a few dozen interactions are enough for noticea...", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/openclaw-rl-trains-ai-agents-simply-by-talking-converting-every-reply-into-a-training-signal/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 5}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=33257", "title": "Hollywood copyright complaints force Bytedance to shelve global launch of AI video generator Seedance 2.0", "summary": "Bytedance planned to launch its AI video model Seedance 2.0 globally in mid-March. That's not happening, because Hollywood's biggest studios have collectively put the brakes on the rollout. The backlash is also a sign of just how convincing AI-generated video has become.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/hollywood-copyright-complaints-force-bytedance-to-shelve-global-launch-of-ai-video-generator-seedance-2-0/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 3}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=33192", "title": "Codewall's AI agent hacked an AI recruiter, then impersonated Trump to test its voice bot's guardrails", "summary": "AI agents can hack systems, defend them, and be hacked themselves. Codewall's one-hour takeover of an AI recruiting platform shows just how tangled this new security landscape has become.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/codewalls-ai-agent-hacked-an-ai-recruiter-then-impersonated-trump-to-test-its-voice-bots-guardrails/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 2}], "today_tech": [{"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.12342v1", "title": "MamTra: A Hybrid Mamba-Transformer Backbone for Speech Synthesis", "summary": "Abstract: Despite the remarkable quality of LLM-based text-to-speech systems, their reliance on autoregressive Transformers leads to quadratic computational complexity, which severely limits practical applications. Linear-time alternatives, notably Mamba, offer a potential remedy; however, they ofte...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.12342", "source": "arXiv Audio & Speech", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.12342v1/2603.12342v1/x1.png", "score": 12}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2603.12382v1", "title": "SPARR